MVP List
FauxTwitterClone, a Twitter clone, is a website for users to share brief thoughts, engage in light discussion, post memes, and spread propaganda.

1. New account creation, log in, log out, and guest/demo login
Users can sign up, log in, log out and browse.
Users can't use certain features without logging in (create posts, like, comment).
If not logged in while interacting with a feature, and message will pop recommending them to either log in or create an account.
Logged in users are directed to the home page.
Logged out users are directed to the login page.


2. Hosting on Heroku


3. Posts
Logged in users can create posts.
Logged in users can edit and delete their own posts.
All users can view a sampling of the most recent posts.
A post can include text, images, section for tags (Bonus: like)

4. Comments
Logged in users can create comments on posts.
Logged in users can edit and delete their own comments.
All users can view comments on posts.

5. Search
All users can see how many users have liked a post or comment.
A user can search by tag.

6. Tags / Topics
Logged in users can add tags to their posts from a pre-defined list, or users can create their own tags.
All users can click on tags to view a list of recent posts that contain that tag.

7.

7. Production README
Brief explanation of what the app is and does.
How to start development environment
Technologies used
Link to live site
Link to Wiki docs
Discussion of two features that show off the team's technical abilities
Discussion of both challenges faced and the way the team solved them
Code snippets to highlight the best code

8. Bonus Features
Display a list of recent commonly used tags.
Users can search for other users to view all of their posts.
Bonus / Likes


